race.comment: ZOUSAIN BOLT (3) showed good pace over 1400m at Beaudesert and dug deep to score in a 65 by a nose. In a top metro barn and will be fitter again. Nicely placed to go back-to-back. HELL AND BACK (1) is in the premier stable and was beaten less than 2L at Eagle Farm in stronger after being in contention on the bend. Won a 62 prior and maps well. The likely danger. HUSSY EMPRESS (9) found the line nicely to grab third at the Sunshine Coast, beaten 1.6L. Will be better for that and can't be ruled out. TESER (2) has switched from a Victorian stable on a 24-day return. Just missed at Bendigo last time and the speedy galloper can use the inside gate. Interests.
